<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-14T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-14T16:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/2225a</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_LIB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d307fn2">The same to the Ambassador in Italy, No. 1764;
                                    unnumbered telegram of notification on the same date to the
                                    Ambassador in France. (File No. 003.1140/—.)</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-14T17:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1967. You may inform the Government to which you are accredited that
                                the President has decided to send Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HEM1">E.
                                    M. House</persName> to Europe as his special representative. Mr.
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HEM1">House</persName> will start almost
                                immediately.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>